text: Øivind Holmsen (28 April 1912 – 23 August 1996) was a Norwegian football player who played for the national team. He was mostly known for winning a bronze medal with his team for placing third at the 1936 Summer Olympics football tournament. ==References== Category:1912 births Category:1996 deaths Category:Norwegian footballers Category:Competitors at the 1936 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic bronze medalists for Norway
